  <div id="text-content_77af08d8-94b5-404c-9e8f-dee08ed9d104" class="text-block-content">
    <p>If the Account and Course Level Outcome Mastery Scales feature option is enabled for your account, mastery scales and calculation methods are separated from individual outcomes, and the Outcomes page displays Mastery Scales and Calculation Methods tabs. </p>
<p>From the Calculation tab, you can set mastery calculation methods for the entire account.</p>
<p><strong>Notes:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Enabling the Account and Course Level Outcome Mastery Scales feature option will affect current account data.</li>
<li>If a rubric with aligned outcomes has been used to assess an assignment before Account and Course Level Outcome Mastery Scales are enabled, the assignment is not affected. However, any assignments that have not been assessed by the rubric are affected if mastery scores are adjusted.</li>
</ul>
  </div>
</div>

      <div class="step screensteps-section screensteps-depth-1" id="open-account" data-step-uuid="5988c913-13ed-4269-94e8-e025776f9840">
